{"description":"Papasmooth is one of a very few who has been here with us since day 1 when abstract is only the concept transitioning from testnet to mainnet

I could personally say that he truly deserves gigachad where he continues to spread positive and supportive energy 

I wish you the best brother"}

{"description":"Aliru is very present within the Abstract ecosystem, he is an active Gigachad, often there to help the community.

He brings his touch of freshness and originality.

I appreciate him for his authenticity."}

{"description":"KangBokSoon is the legend in Korean Gigachad community. He always on top take care Abstract Korea community in telegram chat and contents on X.

I also have a chance to meet him in Korea durng KBW. SUPER NICE GUY

KangBokSoon is super good energy that people want to be around!"}

{"description":"I previously knew Kang Bok Soon for a couple months now from his content on X both English and Korean which he's kinda similar to how I did both to support Abstract and local community as a whole

Once we met personally during KBW, I could say that he's one of the genuine, kind, and nice to people around even we need to use translation showing how he is being really considerate while wanna communicate as much as possible

let's meet more! and I'll try my best to go there for KBW 2026"}

{
  "description": "Absolutely dedicated green chain lover from Africa. Representing chain IRL, contributing in different ways, like writing articles, guides, streams."
}

{
  "description": "Giga Chad energy, reliable, friendly, and incredibly talented. Pavil is easily one of the brightest people in the Pudgy Penguins and Abstract community. I’m an absolute fan of his work, his street art is museum quality, just incredible stuff. LayerZero, Abstract NFTs, and PP are some of my favorite artworks, and seeing how he elevates these spaces is inspiring. A true gem to any community. Big brother penguin. Massive respect, can’t wait for the next art drop.",
  "source": "Ethos Everywhere Wallet",
  "version": "1.0",
  "client": "web"
}

{
  "description": "Pavil's an amazing OG member of the pudgy community, and his art is electric, always excited to see what he whips up next."
}

{
  "description": "Pavil is an incredible street artist which made a huge graffiti artworks for communities like Abstract and Pudgy Penguins, and many others.

Always supportive and have a big heart, deserves a lot of recognition for his work.

It takes a lot of effort to make something like he does, and it brings a lot of positivity and unites the space.

Also, he's done an Ironman triathlon, which takes a lot of preparation and physical health, which is so inspirational."
}

{
  "description": "First time met Berry in Abstract discord, a bit later he joined Huddle. He is from Toronto. Pudgy Canada has strong local community, hope he is going to add value to them. Absolutely welcome. He is mostly focus on Polymarket stuff, easy to call him Polymarket Maxi. He is super supportive chad. Absolutely happy to support him with positive review."
}

{
  "description": "Can't say that we chatted so much, we didn't meet each other in person on any event or conference. AP is one of the leaders from marketing agencys in web3 and Abhi is CEO of it who is always active, plus heard too much positive things about his buildings, about his effort from my close friends. It's impossible to skip positive review for real builders like he."
}

{
  "description": "Pavil is a true giga chad on Abstract Chain, deeply committed to his work, creating stunning street artstyle pieces. You’ve built an amazing community on X."
}

{
  "description": "Pavil been one of the first Penguins I met on the timeline and only can say great things about him. 

His street art is so good really like the way he does those graffitis is just incredible and always showing up to support the penguins.

Definitly someone great to have in your circle."
}

{
  "description": "First meeting has been in Abstract project. Green chain is growing everywhere, great to have so kind, supportive and friendly person from Korea among us. He is managing Korean account, sharing updates, guides. Happy to support with review."
}

{
  "description": "I met sillybilly through onchain heroes. 

sillybilly is an ideal example of what a great community member looks like. his content is great, he shows up and is always positive in the discord/timeline. 

we are very lucky to have him around as a friend"
}

{
  "description": "MIC has been supporting Abstract Chain for a very long time. He always comments and create posts to help promote projects on Abstract.

The consistency is the key of MIC. He is always with Abstract during bull and bear market.

We are so glad to have him!"
}

{
  "description": "I first knew tut by his reply to my post on X about xeet when he dropped his xeetby and I got to see more of his works\n\none of a few artists who creatively build and support the  brand to be easily memorized through different characters"
}
